snippet.textDisplay:
Here is the real problem with China in regards to their spying.
They spy and use the stolen information to undermine other countries markets and in an illegal manner.  Information stolen is not strictly for defense and "intelligence" purpose.    

SHORT EXPLAINATION:  They spy on corporate to steal propietary production design and information.  The information will be passed on to state own (even privately owned) companies/corporation to make a copy or rip-off and sell the products at a lower cost.  
So say a US company invest $3 billion on Research and Develope a product and they must sell it for $100 to recover the cost of R&D.  Now the chinese company can sell the same product for $50 because they spend nothing on R&D.   A customer will just buy the $50 product because it is cheaper.  Now the US company is at a loss because customers are buying the Chinese copied product.

Sure the US, Russia, Germany etc.. spy but they spy for purpose of intelligence and defense in regards to the capability and potential threat from certain countries.  They do not target corporation with primary goal of stealing their propietary information and passing it on to corporations so they have an unfair advantage.

That is the difference that people are not aware of.

snippet.textDisplay: Do you know what bounty hunters do?  Not saying I think it's a good practice for anyone to sell geo data, but bounty hunters are searching for bail jumpers, people accused of crimes who are avoiding court.  While bounty hunters go out and actively seek these criminals thanks to capitalism police will generally not bother, the court will just issue a warrant and the police will just depend on happening across these criminals during their commission of yet another crime.  There are certainly entities I would be far more concerned with having access to that data.
